WEBVTT

00:04.588 --> 00:06.749
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

00:08.258 --> 00:10.294
[CHATTERING]

00:12.680 --> 00:15.387
So it turns out
global warming's just another excuse...

00:15.557 --> 00:17.684
...to take your clothes off.

00:17.851 --> 00:21.719
I know what it looks like, but Oliver claims
they raise ton of money at this thing.

00:21.897 --> 00:24.263
Yeah, at 500 bucks a plate, I'll bet.

00:24.441 --> 00:27.103
I'm just glad you've got your press pass.

00:27.528 --> 00:29.814
Although as much
as I love the one-on-one time...

00:29.988 --> 00:33.321
...I gotta say, I'm actually surprised
Lois unattached you from her hip.

00:33.492 --> 00:35.904
What do you mean?
Lois and l aren't always together.

00:36.078 --> 00:38.820
You see her more than I see Jimmy,
and we're engaged.

00:38.997 --> 00:40.828
What are you trying to say?

00:42.543 --> 00:43.908
Never mind.

00:44.086 --> 00:47.874
I guess I just always thought
that I would be the one circling your typos.

00:48.966 --> 00:52.049
Lois doesn't circle typos.
She underlines them two or three times.

00:53.387 --> 00:55.093
And she couldn't skip out early.

00:55.264 --> 00:58.051
In typical Lois fashion,
she's already on Tess' bad side.

00:58.225 --> 00:59.260
Tess.

00:59.435 --> 01:02.051
That's assuming that the Luthor wannabe
has a good side.

01:02.229 --> 01:05.938
I know she's a diehard Lex supporter,
but up until this point, she's been civil.

01:06.108 --> 01:07.143
Aha.

01:07.317 --> 01:08.477
[CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

01:08.652 --> 01:12.895
And I'm sure the ﬂowing hair and piercing
green eyes didn't sway you at all.

01:13.073 --> 01:15.655
It doesn't change the fact
that Lex knows my secret.

01:15.826 --> 01:19.444
If she truly is following in Lex's footsteps,
then she may not be far behind.

01:19.621 --> 01:22.363
You're right, and if Lex chose her
to carry on his legacy...

01:22.541 --> 01:24.873
...she must be handled
with extreme caution.

01:25.836 --> 01:27.167
WOMAN 1:
| see them. Adrianna.

01:27.337 --> 01:29.419
MAN 1: Adrianna.
WOMAN 2: Can we get a picture please?

01:29.590 --> 01:31.251
MAN 2:
Hell of a week. Look at the turnout.

01:31.800 --> 01:33.415
MAN 3: Oliver.
MAN 4: Smile.

01:33.594 --> 01:36.176
-Oh, that was great.
MAN 2: You guys look great.

01:36.346 --> 01:37.552
[CHATTERING]

01:39.641 --> 01:41.632
MAN 1: Oliver, smile.
WOMAN 1: Oliver.

01:41.810 --> 01:42.845
MAN 2:
Ollie, can we get—?

01:43.020 --> 01:44.305
[GLASS SHATTERS]

01:45.814 --> 01:48.191
Looks like Ollie's party started
in the limo.

01:48.358 --> 01:51.270
No. He'd never show up drunk.

01:59.995 --> 02:01.986
Excuse me. Excuse me.

02:02.164 --> 02:04.371
Oliver, come on. Just stand up.

02:04.541 --> 02:05.792
Hey, back off, back off.

02:05.959 --> 02:08.336
-What?
-I know you're not drunk.

02:08.879 --> 02:12.371
-Come on, let's get you to a hospital.
-No. No hospital, please.

02:12.549 --> 02:14.756
Oliver, what's happened to you?

02:14.927 --> 02:16.042
Poisoned.

02:18.096 --> 02:19.711
l have 12 hours to live.

03:19.449 --> 03:21.110
Chloe, he's getting worse.

03:21.285 --> 03:23.947
If it's poison,
we need to get him go to a hospital.

03:25.163 --> 03:27.370
-Davis is on his way.
-He needs a doctor, Chloe.

03:27.541 --> 03:30.499
Clark, if Oliver said
he wants to avoid all MDs and hospitals...

03:30.669 --> 03:32.534
...l'm sure he has a really good reason.

03:32.713 --> 03:36.126
-l'm not gonna watch my friend die.
-Clark, you think this is easy for me?

03:36.300 --> 03:38.586
I know Oliver too.
I worked side by side with him.

03:38.760 --> 03:41.012
And when he says to do something
it's always for a reason.

03:41.179 --> 03:43.465
But this time it's different.
His life's at stake.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.803
Clark, if you were lying on that couch,
I would do whatever you asked.

03:46.977 --> 03:50.265
I wouldn't hesitate. Now trust him.

03:52.149 --> 03:56.233
Let me check his phone and see if I can ﬁnd
the number of the girl he was with tonight.

04:00.824 --> 04:04.817
-Thank God. Davis.
-He is a lot worse than you said he was.

04:04.995 --> 04:07.611
-We think he may have been poisoned.
-Can you help him?

04:07.831 --> 04:08.911
Uh.

04:10.584 --> 04:13.997
His pulse is racing and he's burning up.

04:14.171 --> 04:17.083
He's stable, so I can set up a heart
monitor and take his blood.

04:17.257 --> 04:20.340
But if things don't look better in one hour,
I gotta bring him in.

04:20.510 --> 04:25.004
I know you're risking yourjob to do this,
but you can trust me.

04:26.058 --> 04:27.173
[SIGHS]

04:28.852 --> 04:31.685
Watch him. If anything changes, call.
I'll get the monitor.

04:34.566 --> 04:36.022
[BUTTONS BEEPING]

04:38.946 --> 04:41.688
His date's name is Adrianna.
It showed up in the calendar.

04:41.865 --> 04:43.901
And she didn't call after he disappeared?

04:44.076 --> 04:47.534
And she won't pick up either.
I'm gonna go and see if she's still there.

04:47.704 --> 04:50.946
Well, let's hope for Oliver's sake
that she knows something.

04:53.085 --> 04:55.701
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

05:00.676 --> 05:01.916
[SIGHS]

05:07.015 --> 05:08.095
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

05:13.271 --> 05:16.058
Latest dish with a side order
of spellcheck.

05:16.233 --> 05:19.691
Grisly murders down on Hampton.

05:22.406 --> 05:25.443
Lois Lane. I haven't ﬁred you yet?

05:25.617 --> 05:27.903
Guess you're too busy
printing my stories.

05:32.165 --> 05:34.030
What's with the Oliver Queen collage?

05:34.209 --> 05:36.951
I ﬁgured the news had trickled down
to the basement by now.

05:37.129 --> 05:40.872
You know, for a renowned party boy,
Queen doesn't know how to hold his liquor.

05:41.883 --> 05:43.089
Unbelievable.

05:43.260 --> 05:45.592
Metropolis may have
its very own Jack the Ripper...

05:45.762 --> 05:48.595
...and you're preoccupied
with smearing a humanitarian.

05:48.765 --> 05:50.221
Do you even know Oliver Queen?

05:51.101 --> 05:52.466
Not like you do.

05:53.562 --> 05:56.599
Come on, you can't tell me
you don't get a twinge of pleasure...

05:56.773 --> 05:59.606
...seeing your ex take a public nosedive.

06:00.110 --> 06:05.104
Look, he's a good person who stands up
against corruption and social injustice.

06:05.282 --> 06:07.113
Wow.

06:07.492 --> 06:10.450
I was gonna offer you the story,
but after that testimonial...

06:10.620 --> 06:13.657
...you're obviously not objective enough
to uncover the rest of it.

06:13.832 --> 06:16.619
It's not exactly a news ﬂash.
You drink, you get drunk.

06:16.793 --> 06:20.035
When someone leaves a club
fall-down drunk, the story only gets better.

06:20.213 --> 06:24.502
I need someone to get to the bottom of this
without suffering an emotional meltdown.

06:24.885 --> 06:27.342
Please. You know,
you need to read your gossip column.

06:27.512 --> 06:30.424
Oliver and I were through a long time ago.
I'll take the story.

06:30.599 --> 06:31.964
Okay.

06:34.436 --> 06:36.176
[FOOTSTEPS]

06:38.190 --> 06:40.647
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

06:48.033 --> 06:49.113
[LINE RINGING]

06:53.663 --> 06:56.655
[PHONE RINGING]

07:04.800 --> 07:07.007
MAN: Let's get her inside.
We have shallow breathing.

07:07.177 --> 07:09.213
Okay, cover her. Cover her.

07:12.516 --> 07:14.052
[PHONE RINGING]

07:15.143 --> 07:16.724
What happened to her?

07:16.895 --> 07:19.511
Someone found her passed out,
OD'd on something or other.

07:19.689 --> 07:21.941
-Did she say anything?
-She's barely breathing.

07:22.109 --> 07:25.021
Lucky if she makes it
to the hospital alive.

07:30.826 --> 07:32.737
Come on, Oliver.

07:32.911 --> 07:36.028
Whatever's going on inside you,
you can beat it.

07:56.601 --> 07:57.932
[G ROANING]

08:17.497 --> 08:19.203
Hello?

08:19.374 --> 08:21.740
Can anyone hear me?

08:37.267 --> 08:38.427
Oh.

08:40.103 --> 08:41.639
All right.

08:41.813 --> 08:43.644
Here's the deal.

08:43.815 --> 08:47.603
Normally, I don't eat anything
with more than 99 legs on it...

08:47.777 --> 08:50.109
...but I haven't eaten for days.

08:50.614 --> 08:53.026
Kind of a bummer for both of us, right?

08:58.747 --> 09:01.113
Uh, okay, you win. Go.

09:01.291 --> 09:03.247
[ANIMAL GRUNTING]

10:32.841 --> 10:34.832
[MOTOR ENGINE REVS]

10:37.595 --> 10:39.210
MAN 1:
They're on the boat.

10:39.389 --> 10:41.721
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

10:41.891 --> 10:44.428
MAN 2: Pull away.
MAN 1: Off the boat.

10:44.602 --> 10:45.978
MAN 3:
Yes, sir, captain.

10:46.146 --> 10:49.434
MAN 1: Everything off the boat.
MAN 3: Aye, aye.

10:49.607 --> 10:53.600
MAN 1: Give me a hand with this, will you?
MAN 2: Okay, I got it.

10:55.363 --> 10:56.569
That's good.

10:56.740 --> 10:59.072
MAN 1:
Now, come on, let's do this.

10:59.242 --> 11:00.903
All right, let's move it.

11:04.164 --> 11:06.450
[GRUNTS]

11:10.628 --> 11:12.368
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

11:14.591 --> 11:15.922
[CHLOE SIGHS]

11:16.259 --> 11:19.751
Hey, have you seen Ollie?
Apparently he's boozed his way into a....

11:21.431 --> 11:23.638
Wow, who has he been partying with,
Motley Criie?

11:23.808 --> 11:26.800
-Lois, it's not what you think.
-Find me a 24-hour market.

11:26.978 --> 11:30.766
I need a sports drink, as much vitamin B
as you can get, and one dill pickle.

11:30.940 --> 11:32.931
Let's go, ticktock.

11:33.109 --> 11:34.974
He's not hung over, Lois.

11:40.950 --> 11:42.110
What's going on?

11:42.285 --> 11:46.574
Clark's trying to ﬁgure it out,
but we do know that it's serious.

11:47.791 --> 11:49.327
He's been poisoned.

11:50.877 --> 11:52.458
My God.

11:56.633 --> 11:58.089
Ollie?

11:58.259 --> 11:59.999
It's Lois.

12:06.476 --> 12:07.886
Hey.

12:09.104 --> 12:11.140
What's he doing here?
He needs a real doctor.

12:11.314 --> 12:12.815
He said no hospitals.

12:12.982 --> 12:15.519
I'm actually conscious,
and I'm saying he needs one.

12:15.693 --> 12:18.025
Lois, I know what it looks like, okay?

12:18.196 --> 12:22.064
But right now Oliver needs people
he can trust, and this is what he wanted.

12:25.870 --> 12:27.155
You're right.

12:27.330 --> 12:31.414
I know Ollie better than anyone,
and if he said no hospitals...

12:31.584 --> 12:32.664
[SIGHS]

12:35.839 --> 12:38.501
...then I guess we have to take his word
for it.

12:44.431 --> 12:47.173
-[WHISPERING] Mercy.
-O||ie?

12:48.143 --> 12:49.178
What are you saying?

12:50.478 --> 12:52.139
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Mercy.

12:52.313 --> 12:53.814
Hey.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.016
Can you hear me?

12:59.696 --> 13:01.527
Can you hear me?

13:15.003 --> 13:16.959
-Get these things off of me.
TESS: Shh. Shh.

13:17.630 --> 13:20.246
-I hate leeches.
TESS: Stay down.

13:20.425 --> 13:21.881
We can't take them off yet.

13:23.845 --> 13:25.255
[GASPS]

13:25.430 --> 13:27.762
What the hell happened? What is this?

13:28.808 --> 13:30.844
You need your rest.

13:39.068 --> 13:40.569
What's going on here?

13:41.237 --> 13:43.649
-What is this?
-l'm Tess.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.814
Okay, I promised them
that I could save you.

13:46.326 --> 13:47.611
With leeches?

13:48.286 --> 13:51.073
They produce a curing enzyme.

13:54.083 --> 13:56.995
You were poisoned
by a very highly toxic plant.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.331
It's not that I don't appreciate
the sentiment.

13:59.506 --> 14:01.997
I know it sounds crazy,
but I'm a marine biologist.

14:02.175 --> 14:03.790
We study this stuff.

14:03.968 --> 14:06.675
Without this enzyme,
you'd be dead in 12 hours.

14:06.971 --> 14:08.802
A hospital would've misdiagnosed you...

14:08.973 --> 14:12.511
...pumped you full of adrenaline,
and killed you instantly.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.594
I guess you're lucky.

14:19.943 --> 14:22.184
And that shotgun at the door?

14:23.404 --> 14:25.110
Should I feel lucky about that too?

14:27.825 --> 14:29.736
My friend and I...

14:31.120 --> 14:32.860
...we've been kidnapped.

14:40.964 --> 14:42.500
[PHONE RINGING]

14:44.175 --> 14:49.135
Davis. I'm looking for Oliver's date.
She was just admitted.

14:49.305 --> 14:51.466
I'm bringing Oliver in.

14:52.308 --> 14:53.593
We need a little more time.

14:53.768 --> 14:55.349
We couldn't identify the poison...

14:55.520 --> 14:59.308
...but it was something that they drank
in the limo on the way to the fundraiser.

14:59.482 --> 15:02.645
-Adrianna's a victim too?
-Was a victim.

15:04.696 --> 15:08.314
She's ﬁne now. We treated her
with adrenaline and her stats evened out.

15:08.491 --> 15:11.699
-Wait, 10 minutes ago she was dying.
-Modem medicine, Clark.

15:11.869 --> 15:14.997
That girl's living proof that Oliver's too sick
to know what he's talking about.

15:15.164 --> 15:16.199
[BEEPING]

15:16.374 --> 15:17.363
[ADRIANA GASPING]

15:17.542 --> 15:19.078
Code blue.

15:19.252 --> 15:20.708
Get a doctor.

15:20.878 --> 15:23.836
Her pupils are completely dilated.
Her fever's through the roof.

15:24.007 --> 15:26.089
We need 40 cc's of nitro now, now.

15:26.926 --> 15:29.383
She's going into shock. Stay with us.

15:31.097 --> 15:32.837
[EKG FLATLINING]

15:51.826 --> 15:55.990
It's not quite the scenario I pictured
if I ever ran into a woman on this island.

15:59.208 --> 16:01.540
Just be glad that it worked.

16:02.712 --> 16:04.122
What did they do to you?

16:07.592 --> 16:12.052
We were in Fiji doing marine research...

16:12.221 --> 16:15.258
...and this speedboat
came out of nowhere...

16:15.433 --> 16:17.139
...and it attacked us.

16:18.227 --> 16:19.353
[WHIMPERING]

16:19.520 --> 16:23.809
They killed everyone. They killed our guide
and three of my classmates.

16:24.734 --> 16:25.940
Well, how many are there?

16:27.445 --> 16:29.606
There's the one at the door...

16:30.406 --> 16:32.192
...and there's a guy named Marcos.

16:32.825 --> 16:35.567
On their way to Thailand,
their boat started taking water...

16:35.745 --> 16:37.906
...so they stopped here to ﬁx it.

16:39.832 --> 16:41.538
How's your friend?

16:42.251 --> 16:44.082
She'll be okay.

16:44.754 --> 16:47.996
We'll all be okay.
We just have to get out of here.

16:55.098 --> 16:57.009
So how's our golden goose?

16:58.434 --> 17:01.016
Oh, you don't think I know who you are?

17:01.729 --> 17:02.935
Oliver Queen.

17:04.148 --> 17:07.436
-No idea what you're talking about.
-You're famous.

17:07.610 --> 17:12.149
Everyone knows you're that rich brat
who took off with his friends on a yacht...

17:12.323 --> 17:15.531
...and partied his way into a shipwreck.

17:15.702 --> 17:19.194
And lucky for us,
not all of you were shark bait.

17:21.874 --> 17:23.080
Whoa.

17:27.505 --> 17:28.790
[G ROANS]

17:28.965 --> 17:31.126
Just let them go, huh?

17:35.263 --> 17:37.219
I have a different idea.

17:41.811 --> 17:44.348
No! Megan!

17:44.522 --> 17:46.433
We'll ransom him for millions.

17:48.151 --> 17:50.733
No, no, no!

17:50.903 --> 17:53.394
If you kill her,
you're gonna have to kill me ﬁrst.

17:54.157 --> 17:56.569
-You're not gonna die for her.
-I have been stuck...

17:56.743 --> 17:59.655
...on this godforsaken island
for two years.

18:00.121 --> 18:02.328
So I ﬁgure if I die...

18:03.624 --> 18:05.910
...at least I die for something.

18:11.215 --> 18:13.501
The boat's almost done.

18:14.927 --> 18:16.883
Then we are out of here.

18:17.054 --> 18:18.180
[SIGHS]

18:24.645 --> 18:27.102
Look at us, the noble couple.

18:29.192 --> 18:33.526
I let you go, and in return,
you were supposed to save the world.

18:34.363 --> 18:36.024
But this, Ollie...

18:37.033 --> 18:39.695
...this isn't saving the world, is it?

18:40.661 --> 18:43.573
This is you backing out
on your end of the deal.

18:50.296 --> 18:51.285
[SIGHS]

18:51.464 --> 18:53.170
You know, maybe....

18:53.674 --> 18:55.881
Maybe we had it wrong.

18:56.886 --> 18:58.547
Maybe our...

19:00.056 --> 19:03.048
...story ends
and neither of us are heroes.

19:04.060 --> 19:07.678
Because you're not the only one
who couldn't hold up his end of the deal.

19:11.067 --> 19:13.058
The truth is...

19:17.907 --> 19:20.523
...sometimes I wonder
if I should have ever let you go.

19:20.701 --> 19:23.488
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

19:27.333 --> 19:28.869
CLARK:
Lois?

19:30.545 --> 19:32.251
How's he doing?

19:49.188 --> 19:51.349
Clark, can I talk to you for a second?

19:56.487 --> 19:58.443
The hospital couldn't identify the poison.

19:58.614 --> 20:00.730
The proﬁle doesn't match
any public database.

20:00.908 --> 20:04.446
How are we supposed to ﬁnd an antidote
to a poison that doesn't have a name?

20:04.620 --> 20:05.655
Name it ourselves.

20:05.830 --> 20:08.947
Cyanobacteria in Oliver's blood
shares a similar molecular makeup...

20:09.125 --> 20:11.958
...to the chloroplasts found
in a ﬂower of the Nen'um genus.

20:12.128 --> 20:14.665
Here. Now, there's only one species
of Nen'um, oleander.

20:14.839 --> 20:16.955
But that doesn't exactly
narrow things down.

20:17.133 --> 20:19.124
-Chloe--
-However, the high concentration...

20:19.302 --> 20:21.759
...of cardioglycosides
rules out several subspecies...

20:21.929 --> 20:25.342
...orienting us in the South Paciﬁc.

20:26.434 --> 20:29.676
-Why are you looking at me like that?
-Like I'm at a Met U lecture?

20:29.854 --> 20:32.971
Chloe, you're the smartest person I know
by a long shot.

20:33.149 --> 20:36.016
But since when can you trace chemicals
from an obscure ﬂower?

20:36.193 --> 20:38.525
It's no big deal.
I'm expanding my knowledge base.

20:38.696 --> 20:39.902
You're getting smarter.

20:41.324 --> 20:44.282
I don't have time
to discuss this with you right now.

20:45.286 --> 20:47.493
[KEYS CLICKING]

20:52.126 --> 20:53.366
What is all this, Chloe?

20:53.544 --> 20:55.956
Thanks to Lex's obsession with toxins
and viruses...

20:56.130 --> 21:00.715
...LuthorCorp has the most comprehensive
collection of organic material on the planet.

21:22.615 --> 21:24.822
You're reading all this, aren't you?

21:28.079 --> 21:29.194
There it is.

21:29.372 --> 21:32.284
If LuthorCorp has this ﬂower,
then they have the antidote.

21:33.960 --> 21:36.417
As much as I appreciate
whatever it is you just did...

21:36.587 --> 21:38.703
...this is all because of Brainiac, isn't it?

21:38.881 --> 21:39.870
All right, I admit it.

21:40.049 --> 21:44.338
After he attacked me, my hacking skills
went from analog to digital.

21:44.512 --> 21:49.176
And whether I like it or not, I can read
and process data at lightning-fast speed.

21:49.350 --> 21:51.841
I know right now you are making a list
in your head...

21:52.019 --> 21:55.352
...of all the possible ways
this could be your fault, but please don't.

21:55.523 --> 21:58.390
If this is because of Brainiac,
we don't know what can happen.

21:58.567 --> 22:00.068
Exactly. No one knows.

22:00.236 --> 22:04.445
So let's not worry about it until we have to.
Clark, this is my life.

22:04.615 --> 22:07.027
For once, some good came
from something horrible.

22:07.201 --> 22:12.195
I'm choosing to look at this as a gift,
one that could help us save Oliver's life.

22:12.373 --> 22:14.364
Now trust me.

22:17.753 --> 22:20.540
I think it's time to call in a favor
with your new boss.

22:29.056 --> 22:30.466
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

22:32.560 --> 22:34.801
It does bring out your eyes.

22:35.938 --> 22:37.053
That tie.

22:40.026 --> 22:43.610
I was wondering if you could help me.
A friend of mine has been poisoned.

22:43.779 --> 22:44.939
Doctors can't help him...

22:45.114 --> 22:48.402
...but I think LuthorCorp owns the lab
that makes the antidote.

22:48.576 --> 22:51.283
Believe me,
my heart goes out to your friend...

22:51.454 --> 22:55.413
...but I don't have some secret stash
of toxins or antidotes.

22:55.583 --> 22:59.451
There must be something you can do.
Lex never abandons a project.

23:00.254 --> 23:02.085
He doesn't, does he?

23:02.256 --> 23:06.295
I'm still catching up on the ones
he's named after constellations.

23:07.011 --> 23:09.468
But if this lab exists,
I don't know about it.

23:09.638 --> 23:11.378
Look, I realize that you're my boss...

23:11.557 --> 23:14.720
...and that yourjob requires a certain level
of secrecy.

23:15.603 --> 23:19.016
But the antidote to this plant
could save my friend's life.

23:28.574 --> 23:31.281
Who exactly is your friend?

23:32.078 --> 23:35.662
His name is Oliver Queen.
He doesn't have much time to live.

23:40.169 --> 23:43.206
I'm not gonna stand here
and lie to you, Clark.

23:43.380 --> 23:45.917
But I can't help you either.

23:46.467 --> 23:50.051
The lab was relocated
to Campo Grande, Brazil.

23:51.472 --> 23:56.341
Even if I made a call,
we'd never get the antidote here in time.

24:18.249 --> 24:20.365
You must be Lois.

24:20.543 --> 24:23.410
You must be the one
who's actually qualiﬁed to do this.

24:26.674 --> 24:28.335
He's dying.

24:31.929 --> 24:33.385
I'm
sorry

24:38.519 --> 24:40.225
Here's what's gonna happen, dimples.

24:40.396 --> 24:43.058
You are going to reach
into that handy little tackle box...

24:43.232 --> 24:44.563
...and pull us out a miracle.

24:44.733 --> 24:47.520
Oliver Queen does not die today.

24:49.113 --> 24:51.729
The best I can do is keep him alive
a few minutes longer.

24:51.907 --> 24:53.192
Then do it.

25:28.861 --> 25:30.192
Hey.

25:32.448 --> 25:35.781
I gave this bracelet to Megan
for her birthday.

25:38.954 --> 25:41.286
She was my best friend.

25:43.709 --> 25:48.954
She was joking around when she said
that she'd wear it till the day that she died.

25:53.552 --> 25:55.668
Okay, easy, easy. Shh.

25:56.138 --> 25:57.719
Let me help.

26:00.809 --> 26:02.310
There you go.

26:03.896 --> 26:05.136
[SOBBING]

26:05.314 --> 26:06.804
Come here.

26:06.982 --> 26:08.847
Shh. Come here.

26:11.820 --> 26:13.776
I'm so sorry.

26:19.328 --> 26:21.159
What are you doing?

26:22.539 --> 26:24.325
They'll kill us.

26:25.042 --> 26:27.954
I swore that
if I ever made it off this island...

26:28.587 --> 26:30.452
...l'd change.

26:32.383 --> 26:34.499
I wouldn't waste my life.

26:40.724 --> 26:42.339
It starts now.

26:47.773 --> 26:49.309
MAN:
Let's go.

26:49.483 --> 26:52.395
The boat's ready. Let's go.

27:08.085 --> 27:09.165
Hurry up.

27:10.296 --> 27:13.038
Careful. That ﬂower's poisonous.

27:27.271 --> 27:28.636
[G ROANING]

27:36.739 --> 27:39.321
You're not gonna leave me here to die.

27:39.491 --> 27:42.699
You wanna live,
you crawl down to the leech pond.

27:42.870 --> 27:44.781
Make some new friends.

27:57.259 --> 27:58.590
You ready to go home?

28:03.932 --> 28:05.843
[BEEPING]

28:06.769 --> 28:08.930
Just hit 106. He's on ﬁre.

28:09.104 --> 28:11.265
Just like Adrianna.
We need more ice and towels.

28:11.440 --> 28:12.771
In the back.

28:14.318 --> 28:17.355
Come on, Ollie. Hold on.

28:17.529 --> 28:19.065
Come on.

28:19.239 --> 28:20.399
[BEEPING RAPIDLY]

28:25.829 --> 28:27.365
He can't take much more of this.

28:32.795 --> 28:34.251
Out of the way.

28:36.799 --> 28:39.085
Lois, I need you to breathe for me.

28:39.843 --> 28:41.299
Breathe.

28:44.723 --> 28:45.963
Come on, Ollie, stay with me.

28:48.602 --> 28:50.308
Clark, he's dying.

28:50.479 --> 28:51.468
Use it.

29:17.172 --> 29:19.549
[MACHINES BEEPING
MORE SLOWLY]

29:28.767 --> 29:31.679
I don't get it. This antidote doesn't exist.

29:31.854 --> 29:34.015
Queen Industries. They have a lab nearby.

29:36.525 --> 29:38.265
Mercy.

29:39.611 --> 29:40.862
You have to go ﬁnd Mercy.

29:41.029 --> 29:43.441
-What?
-Tess Mercer. Clark, please.

29:43.615 --> 29:46.197
Whoever did this to me,
they're gonna go after her next.

29:46.368 --> 29:48.780
-You know Tess?
-There's no time, Clark.

29:48.954 --> 29:51.696
She's working late.
She's at the Daily Planet.

30:08.223 --> 30:09.838
Damn it.

30:22.988 --> 30:24.649
Miss me?

30:25.532 --> 30:28.695
You left me on that island to die.

30:30.662 --> 30:34.075
You're not an easy person to track down,
are you?

30:36.251 --> 30:40.244
There's the scared little girl I remember.

30:41.423 --> 30:44.756
You haven't changed a bit.

30:47.054 --> 30:49.511
I think you'd be surprised.

30:52.726 --> 30:55.092
I meant to write you a postcard
to say thank you.

30:56.396 --> 31:00.264
You were one of the men in my life
that taught me how to ﬁght back.

31:58.667 --> 31:59.827
Really?

32:00.627 --> 32:03.334
What happened to the party boy
hanging up his beer bongs...

32:03.505 --> 32:05.006
...so that he could do good?

32:05.173 --> 32:08.210
-l'm not the guy in that article anymore.
-Course you're not.

32:08.385 --> 32:11.502
You're Oliver Queen,
world-famous Samaritan.

32:11.680 --> 32:13.671
And I was his ﬁrst save.

32:15.142 --> 32:16.882
Excuse me, you, um....

32:27.154 --> 32:29.361
You know you were much more than that.

32:31.908 --> 32:34.570
I'm glad you're okay, Oliver.

32:38.040 --> 32:40.497
I need the chief of Queen Industries
alive and well...

32:40.667 --> 32:43.875
...if LuthorCorp
is gonna keep its competitive edge.

32:45.130 --> 32:46.995
I'm happy to help.

32:47.716 --> 32:49.547
This is great.

32:51.261 --> 32:53.843
A few pay grades up
from your days studying jellyﬁsh...

32:54.014 --> 32:56.050
...and protesting whaler ships, huh?

32:56.224 --> 32:57.600
You're not the ﬁrst person...

32:57.768 --> 33:01.056
...to wonder how I arrived at the helm
of the Luthor dynasty.

33:01.229 --> 33:02.560
Well, what's to wonder?

33:03.106 --> 33:05.222
You play to win.

33:05.901 --> 33:08.859
I found out how ruthless you were
a long time ago.

33:10.113 --> 33:13.901
After what you did to me, did you expect
me to just sit around and eat ice cream?

33:14.076 --> 33:16.158
No, you'd rather work
for my greatest enemy...

33:16.328 --> 33:19.570
...and then, just when I think
the knife can't twist any farther...

33:19.748 --> 33:21.454
...you take over his entire company.

33:21.625 --> 33:22.910
Oh, so that's what you do...

33:23.085 --> 33:25.997
...when you're not writing checks
and grinning for the cameras.

33:26.171 --> 33:30.460
You sit around pondering ways
that I've dedicated my life to your downfall.

33:30.634 --> 33:34.923
I'm sorry to break it to you, Oliver,
but everything I did, I did for me.

33:36.932 --> 33:39.765
Well, then I guess our past is behind us.

33:40.310 --> 33:42.642
It has been
since the day that you said goodbye.

33:43.522 --> 33:44.602
Oh, wait.

33:47.442 --> 33:51.776
-You never actually did, did you?
-ls that why you called me here? Hm?

33:52.447 --> 33:54.904
Because it's on the tip of my tongue.

33:57.953 --> 33:59.363
No.

34:00.247 --> 34:02.112
I called you to give you this.

34:02.541 --> 34:04.782
I realize that Lionel Luthor is dead
and buried...

34:04.960 --> 34:07.702
...but maybe this will help you sleep
at night.

34:32.446 --> 34:33.936
-Lois.
-Hey, thanks, Smallville.

34:34.114 --> 34:37.652
-Starting to get the hang of things here.
-That was....

34:38.201 --> 34:41.659
I spoke to Chloe.
She said you didn't come home last night.

34:41.830 --> 34:42.819
[SIGHS]

34:42.998 --> 34:44.113
So not what you're thinking.

34:44.291 --> 34:47.533
I may have played nurse with Oliver,
but it never progressed to doctor.

34:47.711 --> 34:49.667
I've been working here all night.

34:50.839 --> 34:53.000
"Kitten Adoption Fair This Sunday"?

34:54.426 --> 34:56.542
You gave up your article on Oliver
for this?

34:59.347 --> 35:01.633
Doesn't sound like you, Lois.

35:02.517 --> 35:06.635
Is it possible you were more shaken up
about last night than you realized?

35:06.813 --> 35:08.189
You think?

35:08.982 --> 35:11.724
I was practically a three-shot martini.

35:11.902 --> 35:15.565
Yeah, but it doesn't mean you have
to bury your emotions in your work.

35:15.739 --> 35:19.231
This will be the most heartbreaking
kitten-adoption story you've ever read.

35:22.370 --> 35:25.328
-What am I doing? Ollie and I are through.
-Maybe.

35:25.499 --> 35:29.037
But just because your relationship's over
doesn't mean the feelings go away.

35:29.211 --> 35:32.920
I'd be lying ifl said I didn't watch the
goodbye tape Lana sent more than once.

35:33.089 --> 35:37.549
Well, I'd rather avoid a ride
on the Clark-and-Lana roller coaster.

35:37.719 --> 35:39.050
No offense.

35:40.222 --> 35:41.883
It's okay.

35:42.057 --> 35:44.013
I've got a delicate enough ego as it is.

35:44.184 --> 35:47.893
I am not cut out to date a guy
with a hero complex.

35:48.563 --> 35:49.939
I mean, you were there.

35:50.106 --> 35:53.098
You saw him at the fundraiser.
He's an icon, the Man of Tomorrow.

35:53.276 --> 35:56.234
And I'm just Lois Lane,
the girl who writes about it.

35:59.449 --> 36:01.360
-There's nothing wrong with that.
-Right.

36:01.535 --> 36:06.620
So when the occasional feelings ﬂare up,
you gotta trust your gut, as hard as it is...

36:06.790 --> 36:10.248
...and realize that you broke up
for a reason.

36:11.336 --> 36:12.416
Exactly.

36:13.004 --> 36:14.084
[SIGHS]

36:14.256 --> 36:15.917
That one's on the house, Smallville.

36:16.883 --> 36:20.421
You should know, I'm allergic to cats.

36:22.055 --> 36:25.092
Get to work. Chop-chop.

36:43.159 --> 36:44.569
I thought I closed those.

36:45.829 --> 36:48.866
-l'm sorry, they were open.
-What are you doing here?

36:49.040 --> 36:52.123
Uh, well, I was checking in on Oliver.

36:52.294 --> 36:56.458
It was a hell of a close call last night.
He's got a pretty great crew of friends.

36:56.631 --> 36:59.168
Renegade paramedic included.

36:59.342 --> 37:01.333
You must have done pretty well
on your SATs.

37:01.511 --> 37:03.467
I thought you said you studied journalism.

37:03.638 --> 37:05.970
Yeah, journalism,
and then the core classes...

37:06.141 --> 37:08.302
...and some, you know,
electives and stuff.

37:08.476 --> 37:10.728
Level with me, Chloe.
Are you some kind of genius?

37:10.896 --> 37:12.261
I'm embarrassing you.

37:13.857 --> 37:15.973
There's a reason I keep the doors closed.

37:16.151 --> 37:18.893
You know,
there's nothing wrong with being smart.

37:19.404 --> 37:23.067
When the seating chart at your wedding
looks more like a Euclidean algorithm...

37:23.241 --> 37:26.825
...than a dining hall, you know
you've got something seriously wrong.

37:27.996 --> 37:29.031
[DRAWER CLOSES]

37:30.373 --> 37:32.489
And the guy next to you
on that seating chart?

37:32.667 --> 37:34.328
What does he think about all this?

37:37.839 --> 37:39.170
He doesn't know.

37:41.217 --> 37:43.424
Well, it's all sort of just happening.

37:43.595 --> 37:47.053
Which is why I would really prefer it
if we could keep it between us.

37:48.266 --> 37:50.848
Look, Chloe,
I think that in some weird way...

37:51.019 --> 37:54.682
...we all have some part of us
that we hold underneath the surface.

37:57.275 --> 37:59.391
I'll bet even I do.

38:00.070 --> 38:01.480
[CH UCKLES]

38:02.697 --> 38:04.608
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

38:04.783 --> 38:06.944
[CHATTERING]

38:12.874 --> 38:16.116
So I hear I'm not the only one in town
who owes you a drink.

38:16.294 --> 38:19.252
Tess Mercer's attacker was arrested
last night.

38:20.757 --> 38:23.590
Why didn't you tell me
you knew Tess Mercer before?

38:25.553 --> 38:27.089
It was in the past.

38:27.681 --> 38:30.047
I'm not exactly proud
of the way things turned out.

38:30.558 --> 38:33.721
Doesn't change the fact
that she knew the guy who tried to kill you.

38:33.895 --> 38:36.386
Yeah, well, it makes sense to me.

38:36.564 --> 38:39.226
The guy came after me,
then he's gonna go after her.

38:39.401 --> 38:41.733
She's the other captain of industry
in town, so....

38:42.904 --> 38:46.692
With all that poison in your system,
are you sure adding more is the best idea?

38:47.242 --> 38:49.904
Yeah, Clark, why don't you stick
to your milk shakes, huh?

38:59.838 --> 39:01.544
Lionel Luthor killed my parents.

39:03.174 --> 39:07.042
You ﬁgured that out from ﬂight records?
I mean, it was a plane crash.

39:08.138 --> 39:11.005
Yeah, it was a plane crash,
and according to that...

39:11.182 --> 39:13.924
...there were LuthorCorp employees
on the maintenance log.

39:14.102 --> 39:16.434
You think Lionel paid them
to sabotage the plane?

39:23.111 --> 39:24.271
Did you know about this?

39:29.451 --> 39:32.659
You were the son Lionel never had.
The guy knew everything about you.

39:32.829 --> 39:34.285
Don't stand there and tell me...

39:34.456 --> 39:37.289
...that you didn't know
a couple of his dirty little secrets.

39:47.635 --> 39:50.593
Look, Oliver, I was afraid
that you'd do something you'd regret.

39:50.764 --> 39:52.675
Something I regret? Like what, Clark?

39:52.849 --> 39:55.465
You thought I was gonna kill him?
Is that it?

39:56.186 --> 39:58.393
I wouldn't have killed him.

39:59.898 --> 40:03.390
I survived for two years on an island
by myself, Clark.

40:03.568 --> 40:05.900
When it wasn't pouring rain,
it was blistering sun.

40:06.071 --> 40:09.108
There were mosquitoes that ate me alive.

40:11.534 --> 40:14.446
It's okay, because you know what?
It made me strong.

40:15.246 --> 40:19.159
You may be invincible,
but you are not fearless, are you?

40:19.834 --> 40:21.870
You're afraid to trust your friends...

40:22.045 --> 40:25.128
...and you're afraid to face
who you were really meant to be.

40:27.967 --> 40:29.832
You're afraid of everything.

40:31.346 --> 40:33.632
Maybe you haven't been put
to the test yet.

40:34.933 --> 40:37.219
Maybe your island's still out there, Clark.

40:45.652 --> 40:48.064
Take me to the airport, all right?

40:55.954 --> 40:58.195
What the hell?

41:01.042 --> 41:02.248
You.

41:02.794 --> 41:04.375
Who do you think paid your bail?

41:07.173 --> 41:09.209
Jail's too good for you.

41:18.101 --> 41:21.093
He's having a heart attack.
Might wanna take him to the hospital.

41:21.271 --> 41:22.386
What am I, an ambulance?

41:23.481 --> 41:25.517
They'll know what to do with him.

41:42.917 --> 41:46.159
[CAR ENGINE REVS]

42:32.842 --> 42:34.833
[ENGLISH SDH]
